The paper proposes a new segmentation method for analyzing myocardial contrast echocardiography data. The method utilizes a statistical shape model of the myocardium to guide the Random Forest segmentation. This involves introducing a novel Shape Model feature and fitting the shape model to the RF probability map to refine and constrain the final segmentation. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it deals with image segmentation. It is also likely to belong to the Medical Imaging (cs.MED) sub-category, as it deals with analyzing medical images. The paper also utilizes machine learning techniques, specifically Random Forests, which suggests it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the early detection of coronary artery diseases, which suggests it could belong to the Bioinformatics (cs.BIO) sub-category.
